ASSIGNMENT 1: GIT (VERY CLEAR STEPS)
🔹 Step 1: Open VS Code
Open VS Code
Click File → Open Folder
Click New Folder
Name it: LibrarySystem
Click Select Folder
🔹 Step 2: Open Terminal
Click Terminal (top menu)
Click New Terminal
Terminal opens at bottom
🔹 Step 3: Initialize Git

👉 Type in terminal:

git init

✅ This creates a Git repository

🔹 Step 4: Create Python File
Go to left panel (Explorer)
Click New File icon
Type: app.py
Press Enter

👉 Open file and type:

print("Hello Library")

👉 Save:

Press Ctrl + S
🔹 Step 5: Add and Commit

👉 In terminal:

git add app.py
git commit -m "first commit"

✅ File is saved in Git

🔹 Step 6: Modify and Track
Open app.py
Change code (add another print)

👉 Then:

git diff
git add app.py
git commit -m "updated file"
git log
🔹 Step 7: Create Branch
git branch feature
git checkout feature

👉 Modify file → then:

git add .
git commit -m "feature added"
git checkout main
🔹 Step 8: Merge
git merge feature
🔹 Step 9: Push to GitHub
Open GitHub in browser
Click New Repository
Copy repo URL

👉 In terminal:

git remote add origin <URL>
git push -u origin main
